Chelsea manager, Frank Lampard, has demanded more goals from his striker, Tammy Abraham. Chelsea face Wolves in a Premier League clash at the Molineux, on Saturday. Lampard said he wants more from the England U21 star who has scored four goals already this season. Abrahim’s four goals came in his last two starts for Chelsea and the young star will be in line to make the XI against Wolves. Lampard told reporters at the pre-match conference on Saturday, “Very good, and I am delighted for Tammy. “His enthusiasm and the goals, similar to Mason I want more and he wants more. Everyone needs to be ready.” Chelsea occupy the 11th position in the Premier League table. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.